really alpha right now.
Work only on xterm compatible terminal.
Syntax highligh is correct for C only.

Commands :

^Q Quit
^S Save

^U Undo
^R Redo/Repeat
^T repeat/replace Till current line/occurence

^A (begin) begin of line
^E (end) end of line
^B Back one word
^F Forward one word

^D (del) del character under cursor
^H (backspace) del character before cursor

^L del to end of Line
^K Kill word before

^@ (^space) start Selection
^C copy line/selection
^X cut line/selection
^V paste at cursor position

^W Where is : enter search pattern (previous one if empty)
^Y search first (current or id under cursor)
^N search Next (current or id under cursor)
^P search Previous (current or id under cursor)

^G Goto line (0 is the last one)
^J Justify
^I (tab) Indent/complete
^M (enter)
^O Open line before
^Z change case and avance right

^[ (esc) cancel current command
^] (insert) insert next char litteraly

^_ ??
^\ ??
^^ ??

(arrow keys) move around
(pgup) move by an half screen up
(pgdown) move by an half screen down

Flags :

F1  line number (+redraw)
F2  auto indent
F3  ??
F4  ??
